{{Infobox protected area | name = Alúvium Blhu | iucn_category = III | photo = | photo_caption = | area = 0,0279 km²<ref name="official">[http://uzemia.enviroportal.sk/main/detail/cislo/770 ''Štátny zoznam osobitne chránených častí prírody SR''] {{sk icon}}</ref> | established = 1991 | visitation_num = | visitation_year = | governing_body = ŠOP - S-CHKO Cerová vrchovina |external_link = }}
'''Alúvium Blhu''' is a nature reserve in the [[Slovakia|Slovak]] county of [[Rimavská Sobota]] in the municipality of [[Hrušovo]]. It covers an area of 2,79 ha and has a protection level of 4 under the slovak law. It is part of the [[Cerová vrchovina Protected Landscape Area]]<ref name="official" />
==Description== Alúvium Blhu was created for the protection of [[alder]] stands. The area is important for scientific research.<ref name="official" />
==Flora== One of the protected plants in the area is the [[ostrich fern]] that occurs here in dense concentrations. This fern is a protected and very endangered species in Slovakia<ref name="official" />
