'''Dominic Couzens''' is a British [[birders|birder]], author and journalist specialising in [[bird|avian]] and [[natural history]] subjects.<ref name="Pearson">Pearson, Louisa (2005) "[http://news.scotsman.com/features/Birds-of-a-feather.2660013.jp Birds of a Feather]", ''[[The Scotsman]], 10 September 2005, retrieved 2010-12-04</ref>

He contributes regularly to ''[[Bird Watching (magazine)|Bird Watching]]'' and ''[[BBC Wildlife]]'' magazines; and is also a professional [[field trip]] guide. His books ''The Secret Lives of Garden Birds'', ''The Secret Lives of British Birds'', and ''The Secret Lives of Garden Wildlife'' all received praise, with the former selected by ''[[The Guardian]]'' as one of the best wildlife books of 2004,<ref name="Moss">Moss, Stephen (2004) "[https://www.theguardian.com/books/2004/dec/04/bestbooksoftheyear.scienceandnature Doing what comes naturalistically: Stephen Moss on the best wildlife books of 2004]", ''[[The Guardian]]'', 4 December 2004, retrieved 2010-12-04</ref> an accolade also received by ''the Secret Lives of British Birds'',<ref name="Moss2">Moss, Stephen (2006) "[https://www.theguardian.com/books/2006/nov/25/scienceandnature.bestbooksoftheyear The call of the wild: Stephen Moss goes foraging for the best of the year's nature books]", ''[[The Guardian]]'', 25 November 2006, retrieved 2010-12-04</ref> and the latter picked as one of the best new nature books of Spring 2008 by ''[[The Times]]''.<ref name="May">May, Derwent (2008) "[http://entertainment.timesonline.co.uk/tol/arts_and_entertainment/books/non-fiction/article3987052.ece The best new nature books for Spring]", ''[[The Times]]'', 22 May 2008, retrieved 2010-12-04</ref>

